7c-f6cbad8cc855?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8=
ExkRNpU ] that it was partnering with Coinbase to bring faster, cheaper Bas=
e infrastructure to its customers. In the face of overzealous regulators, c=
rypto entrepreneurs continue to fight to make capitalism more effective [ h=
ttps://substack.com/redirect/10f7662a-eeb9-4b69-b525-2f2220410d16?j=3DeyJ1I=
joiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ].=C2=A0
And in nuclear, entrepreneurs are pushing ahead with new reactor designs an=
d manufacturing processes despite the fact that the Nuclear Regulatory Comm=
ission (NRC) has not approved a new reactor design in its entire existence.=
=C2=A0
I moderated a panel on Energy at Reindustrialize last week with JC Btaiche =
from Fuse [ https://substack.com/redirect/2645b8e0-2694-4422-9071-534f8b064=
f89?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], D=
oug Bernauer from Radiant [ https://substack.com/redirect/39d62093-9dbc-43e=
6-889e-7ef2d30f81a4?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8=
-6m8ExkRNpU ], and Isaiah Taylor from Valar Atomics [ https://substack.com/=
redirect/eaec87b6-eff2-4503-bc5b-92075c4c83ea?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T=
7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], and what struck me once again is h=
ow hard it is to get nuclear founders to place any blame on the NRC. Instea=
d, they see regulation as just one of the many challenges they need to solv=
e in order to bring cheap, abundant clean energy to millions of people, and=
 reap the rewards if they do so.=C2=A0
Even when the government puts up roadblocks to progress, the American syste=
m and the American spirit are such that entrepreneurs simply take it upon t=
hemselves to get around them.=C2=A0
You Can Just Build Things=C2=A0
No one is coming to save us.
You can just build things.=C2=A0
Those two phrases, which frequently appear in my X feed, are as optimistic =
as it gets.=C2=A0
As universities, legacy media, and traditional institutions crumble, as the=
 government becomes ever more tangled in red tape, as two octogenarians duk=
e it out to become the leader of the free world, America is built in such a=
 way that entrepreneurs can just build things. And as the tools that entrep=
reneurs have at their disposal continue to improve [ https://substack.com/r=
edirect/fddc36fb-4f75-4916-a203-85782dfbb6d1?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7=
GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], progress can continue to accelerate=
 even as institutions stumble.=C2=A0
In fact, because technology compounds at a faster rate than legacy institut=
ions, I=E2=80=99d expect that the share of responsibility for the continuat=
ion of the American Empire will continue to shift in the entrepreneurs=E2=
=80=99 direction.=C2=A0
To the extent that it is an empire, America is an empire defined not by its=
 ability to expand geographically to capture existing resources, but by its=
 ability to expand technologically to create new ones. America, therefore, =
is a boundless empire.=C2=A0
We will see more legacy institutions fall and weaken, and it may feel chaot=
ic. Good! That chaos, underpinned by a stable Constitution and legal code, =
is the lifeblood of America=E2=80=99s success. The greater the challenges, =
the bigger the opportunities, the better the solutions.=C2=A0
We can even build new and better institutions to replace old and sclerotic =
ones.=C2=A0
Just last week, Arc Institute, a new kind of scientific research organizati=
on, announced [ https://substack.com/redirect/4a12a345-b744-4a3d-ad14-2dd9a=
f8c4aa3?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU =
] that it had =E2=80=9Cdiscovered a compact and entirely new type of progra=
mmable molecular system that evolved to directly insert new DNA sequences i=
nto the genome using bridge RNAs =E2=80=93 a new class of guide RNAs.=E2=80=
=9D The announcement was notable for both the science, and the institution =
that discovered it.=C2=A0
On Sunday, Pirate Wires=E2=80=99 Mike Solana penned We Are the Media Now [ =
https://substack.com/redirect/0580df10-520f-4055-bf4b-d27c0248013a?j=3DeyJ1=
IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] about the impo=
rtance of building new media. He wrote:=C2=A0
=E2=80=9CThe Old Things are what they are, and will always be thus. To buil=
d something truly new, you have to build it from scratch.=E2=80=9D
We can and will build new things from scratch on top of stable American inf=
rastructure.=C2=A0
We can and will create the American Millennium.
The American Millennium
In that Newsroom scene, after rattling those statistics, McAvoy pauses, mis=
ty-eyed, before talking about how good we were:
It sure used to be. We stood up for what was right. We fought for moral rea=
sons. We passed laws, struck down laws, for moral reasons. We waged war on =
poverty, not poor people. We sacrificed. We cared about our neighbors. We p=
ut our money where our mouths were and we never beat our chests. We built g=
reat big things, made ungodly technological advances, explored the universe=
, cured disease, and we cultivated the world=E2=80=99s greatest artists and=
 the world=E2=80=99s greatest economy. We reached for the stars.=C2=A0
Good news, Will.=C2=A0
We build great big things to explore the universe=E2=80=A6=C2=A0
We make ungodly technological advances=E2=80=A6=C2=A0
We cure disease. In just the last few weeks in the Weekly Dose of Optimism,=
 we=E2=80=99ve covered gene therapies for hereditary deafness [ https://sub=
stack.com/redirect/c29859c3-2a7a-4640-ad79-4e7185a8b576?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3Q=
ifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] and blindness [ https://s=
ubstack.com/redirect/91979787-755b-423c-8807-a1c86f308bcd?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ=
3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], mRNA cancer vaccines [=
 https://substack.com/redirect/50d59495-526c-4ea9-99a1-e4009fa4c86b?j=3DeyJ=
1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], and breakthr=
oughs in cryonics [ https://substack.com/redirect/240c9244-b99e-4e28-abfa-6=
f0f74117399?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkR=
NpU ], among many others.=C2=A0
And as highlighted earlier in the piece, we=E2=80=99ve done all of this whi=
le building the world=E2=80=99s greatest economy. I=E2=80=99m not qualified=
 to address the quality of our artists, but I will note that America=E2=80=
=99s own Taylor Swift has sold out stadiums in fifteen countries on five co=
ntinents, and has boosted local economies [ https://substack.com/redirect/7=
c47c703-08ac-493a-9a42-a267b51650a4?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNua=
MZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] by hundreds of millions of dollars in many of=
 those countries.=C2=A0
We have done all of this despite a political landscape that feels as dysfun=
ctional as it=E2=80=99s ever been. It doesn=E2=80=99t have to be that way, =
and I don=E2=80=99t believe that it always will.=C2=A0
On Thursday, the Supreme Court struck down Chevron deference [ https://subs=
tack.com/redirect/5ee74d8d-2d11-4ba7-84b4-0ea4a2c46186?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3Qi=
fQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], placing more power back i=
n the hands of the lawmaking process and less in the hands of capricious re=
gulators. It=E2=80=99s another step in the direction of strengthening our c=
ountry=E2=80=99s infrastructure and making it resilient to the whims of any=
 one person or group of people.=C2=A0=C2=A0
There are thousands of great people in the government who want to see the p=
rogress that all of us want to see, and are fighting to make it happen. We =
will have bad Presidents, but we will have great ones again, too. Progress =
will be greatest when the government and entrepreneurs pull in the same dir=
ection.=C2=A0
Companies can=E2=80=99t solve everything, obviously. Good government is cri=
tical. But no matter who is in office, we will progress. It=E2=80=99s what =
America does, and what America will continue to do.=C2=A0
The American Empire isn=E2=80=99t over. It=E2=80=99s just beginning. This w=
ill be the American Millennium as long as Americans believe that they can t=
ake matters into their own hands, build solutions to the challenges that we=
 will inevitably face, and continuously rebuild a better America, and a bet=
ter world.=C2=A0
So go throw on your finest red, white, and blue, crack open a cold one, rel=
ease a flock of Bald Eagles, and celebrate the Fourth of July in the greate=
st country the world has ever known.=C2=A0
Then get back to work.=C2=A0
God bless you, and God bless the United States of America.
Thanks to Dan [ https://substack.com/redirect/8d60523f-f93b-452c-93bc-49eaa=
10a5d64?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU =
] and Claude [ https://substack.com/redirect/ec692185-a2b0-4353-ad9c-5e1fd5=
1dd970?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]=
 for editing.=20
That=E2=80=99s all for today. Have a great 4th of July. We=E2=80=99ll be ba=
ck in your inbox with a Weekly Dose on Friday.=20
Thanks for reading,
Packy

